INSTALLATION INTRODUCTION
-------------------------

 This file describes how to compile and install Iris on your
 system.

REQUIREMENTS
------------

  * ANSI C++ compiler with STL support
  * CMake building system (http://www.cmake.org/)
  * Ragel State Machine Compiler (http://www.complang.org/ragel/)
  * LibEv event loop library (http://software.schmorp.de/pkg/libev.html)
  * Libuud library, used to generate unique identifiers for objects

  For most systems, execute the following to compile and install Iris:

  cmake .
  make
  make install

  If you want to run tests, execute "make test" command.

  To clean package, run "./ClearPackage.sh" script.

CONFIGURATION OPTIONS
---------------------

  DEBUG_MODE - enable/disable debug output
  ENABLE_OPTIMIZATION - enable/disable optimization (gcc only)
  SKIP_RELINK_RPATH - skip relinking and full RPATH for the install tree
  ENABLE_TEST_COVERAGE -enable/disable test coverage (gcc only)

